Feh. Money is money. <br>
<br>
People with this much money to throw away on EQ could mean: <br>
<br>
1) an affluent adult with good income, probably owns his/her own company, is mature, probably has spouse and family, and can easily throw away $40 per month to play a game more addicting than cocaine<br>
<br>
2) a spoiled 13-year old leet d00d powergamer who has millionare parents, a kid that happens to be a griefer type player, because he is used to getting anything he wants, his world, his way, any way he likes it ....and he will find that Legends Server will be absolute heaven for him, and he will convince his entire existing uber guild to migrate to this server <br>
<br>
3) Osama bin Laden got really bored, and cable modem service just arrived in Pakistan, and Osama wanted to do something fun before he knows the USA will catch him.... so he will try out the new EQ Legends Server. <br>
<br>
4) or anything in between #1 and #2, but not #3 <br>
<br>
5) I could be completely wrong, and what really ends up happening is that this new server is populated with 100% polite mature respectful well-bathed, good-smelling role players who have manners, who have great game ethics, and they all have $80,000 a year jobs that can support them for their EQ premium monthly fees.  <br>
<br>
Money can bring out the best in people, and also bring out the worst in people. Apparently, having lots of disposable income is a requirement for playing in this new Legends Server. Role playing is not a requirement apparently. <br>
<br>
Verant.... they sure know how to make money! That's the only thing that cannot be argued here.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
